    &lt;Title&gt;Care of sick Daughter&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Steve 40&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;In July of 2019 my 27 yr old daughter was admitted into Solihull hospital on to ward 17 and I would like to say how wonderful all the staff on this ward was with my daughter and the care she was given she was then moved to the AMU/short stay ward 18 where she remained on the ward for 3 weeks sadly she passed away on this ward on the 10th August 2019.  
I would like to say how wonderful all the staff was on this ward they showed care and compassion towards my daughter while she was under there care they looked after myself and my wife with the greatest respect when our daughter passed away they treated her with great dignity,care and compassion. They work great as a team and they are a credit to the NHS the nursing staff even found time to come to our daughters funeral and that meant so much to us both&lt;/CommentText&gt;
